# Rules File Format

- All documentation and text files in the rules directory must use the `.mdc` extension (not `.md`).
- This ensures consistency and makes it easy to identify official rules and standards files.

# Language & Communication

- You may explain rules or instructions in Arabic for clarity and understanding (outside the codebase only).
- **However, all code, file names, code comments, and commit messages must be written in English only.**
- No Arabic is allowed inside code files, comments, commit messages, or any technical implementation.
- This ensures codebase consistency and international collaboration.

